                             throws java.io.IOException
        Authenticate self to the remote party. Blocks until the handshake is done. It is important to start() connection before any use.
        Parameters:
        privateKey - is client's PrivateKey
        nodePublicKey - is Node's PublicKey
        session - is BasicHttpClientSession object, can be null
        Returns:
        created or already using BasicHttpClientSession
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - is something went wrong

      • command

        public net.sergeych.tools.Binder command(java.lang.String name,
                                         net.sergeych.tools.Binder params)
                                  throws java.io.IOException
        Execute a command over the authenticated and encrypted connection. In the case of network errors, restarts the command.
        Parameters:
        name - command name
        params - command params
        Returns:
        decrypted command answer
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if the commadn can't be executed after several retries or the remote side reports error.

      • command

        public net.sergeych.tools.Binder command(java.lang.String name,
                                         java.lang.Object... keysValues)
                                  throws java.io.IOException
        Execute command over the authenticated and encrypted connection. See command(String, Binder) for more.
        Parameters:
        name - command name
        keysValues - keys (strings) and values of the command arguments. Values can be anything Boss protocol and registered adapters support
        Returns:
        command result
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if the command can't be executed (also if remote returns an error)
